// SCENARIO ANALYSIS (without tests — Spring Security handles these automatically):
// 1. Invalid signature: Spring Security's JwtDecoder throws JwtException
//    → BearerTokenAuthenticationEntryPoint → 401 Unauthorized
//    Response header: WWW-Authenticate: Bearer error='invalid_token'
//
// 2. Expired JWT: JwtDecoder throws JwtExpiredException (a JwtException)
//    → 401 Unauthorized
//    WWW-Authenticate: Bearer error='invalid_token', error_description='Token expired'
//
// 3. Issuer mismatch: JwtDecoder validates 'iss' claim against configured issuer-uri
//    → JwtException → 401 Unauthorized
//
// 4. Wrong role (@PreAuthorize fails): valid JWT, valid signature, but role check fails
//    → AccessDeniedException → 403 Forbidden (not 401!)
//    401 = not authenticated; 403 = authenticated but not authorized
//
// 5. No JWT: BearerTokenAuthenticationEntryPoint
//    → 401 Unauthorized
//    WWW-Authenticate: Bearer realm='razorpay'

